This is the README file for Guido - A Perl/Tk GUI Builder

For information related to this particular release of Guido and changes in this release, see the RELEASE file.  For previous release notes, see HISTORY.

For the change history, see CHANGELOG.

To install Guido, read the INSTALLATION file.  This will tell you how to install the application.

For end user help, a user guide is available in the ./help subdirectory.

If you want to know more about how Guido works internally, you are welcome to read the DESIGN document, the other documentation in the ./doc subdirectory, run perldoc on the Guido modules, or simply read the source code.

For more information or to report bugs in Guido, please visit our project site at http://www.sourceforge.net/projects/guido/